SGE_QMASTER(8)        Grid Engine Administrative Commands       SGE_QMASTER(8)



NNAAMMEE
       sge_qmaster - Grid Engine master control daemon

SSYYNNOOPPSSIISS
       ssggee__qqmmaasstteerr [ --hheellpp ]

DDEESSCCRRIIPPTTIIOONN
       _s_g_e___q_m_a_s_t_e_r controls the overall Grid Engine behavior in a cluster.

OOPPTTIIOONNSS
       --hheellpp  Prints  a listing of all options.

EENNVVIIRROONNMMEENNTTAALL VVAARRIIAABBLLEESS
       SSGGEE__RROOOOTT       Specifies  the location of the Grid Engine standard con-
                      figuration files.

       SSGGEE__CCEELLLL       If set, specifies  the  default  Grid  Engine  cell.  To
                      address a Grid Engine cell _s_g_e___q_m_a_s_t_e_r uses (in order of
                      precedence):

                             The name of the cell specified in the environment
                             variable SGE_CELL, if it is set.

                             The name of the default cell, i.e. ddeeffaauulltt.


       SSGGEE__DDEEBBUUGG__LLEEVVEELL
                      If set, specifies that debug information should be writ-
                      ten to stderr. In addition, the level of detail in which
                      debug information is generated is defined by the defined
                      value.

       SSGGEE__DDEEBBUUGG__LLEEVVEELL
                      If set, the qmaster will not daemonize.

       SSGGEE__QQMMAASSTTEERR__PPOORRTT
                      If set, specifies the tcp port on  which  _s_g_e___q_m_a_s_t_e_r(8)
                      is  expected to listen for communication requests.  Most
                      installations will use a services map entry for the ser-
                      vice "sge_qmaster" instead to define that port.

       SSGGEE__EEXXEECCDD__PPOORRTT If  set, specifies the tcp port on which _s_g_e___e_x_e_c_d(8) is
                      expected to listen  for  communication  requests.   Most
                      installations will use a services map entry for the ser-
                      vice "sge_execd" instead to define that port.

       SSGGEE__TTEESSTT__DDEELLAAYY__SSCCHHEEDDUULLIINNGG
                      If set, specifies a delay in (integral seconds) before a
                      scheduling run, for test purposes.

RREESSTTRRIICCTTIIOONNSS
       _s_g_e___q_m_a_s_t_e_r is usually started from root on the master or shadow master
       machines of the cluster (refer to  the  _G_r_i_d  _E_n_g_i_n_e  _I_n_s_t_a_l_l_a_t_i_o_n  _a_n_d
       _A_d_m_i_n_i_s_t_r_a_t_i_o_n  _G_u_i_d_e  for  more information about the configuration of
       shadow master hosts).  If started by a  normal  user,  a  master  spool
       directory must be used to which the user has read/write access. In this
       case only jobs being submitted by that same user are handled  correctly
       by the system.

FFIILLEESS
       _<_s_g_e___r_o_o_t_>_/_<_c_e_l_l_>_/_c_o_m_m_o_n_/_c_o_n_f_i_g_u_r_a_t_i_o_n
                       Grid Engine global configuration
       _<_s_g_e___r_o_o_t_>_/_<_c_e_l_l_>_/_c_o_m_m_o_n_/_l_o_c_a_l___c_o_n_f_/_<_h_o_s_t_>
                       Grid Engine host specific configuration
       _<_s_g_e___r_o_o_t_>_/_<_c_e_l_l_>_/_c_o_m_m_o_n_/_q_m_a_s_t_e_r___a_r_g_s
                       _s_g_e___q_m_a_s_t_e_r argument file
       _<_s_g_e___r_o_o_t_>_/_<_c_e_l_l_>_/_s_p_o_o_l
                       Default master spool directory

SSEEEE AALLSSOO
       _s_g_e___i_n_t_r_o(1),  _s_g_e___c_o_n_f(5),  _s_g_e___e_x_e_c_d(8),  _s_g_e___s_h_a_d_o_w_d(8), _G_r_i_d _E_n_g_i_n_e
       _I_n_s_t_a_l_l_a_t_i_o_n _a_n_d _A_d_m_i_n_i_s_t_r_a_t_i_o_n _G_u_i_d_e

CCOOPPYYRRIIGGHHTT
       See _s_g_e___i_n_t_r_o(1) for a full statement of rights and permissions.



